metadata.name: Durga Devi
metadata.description:
In Indian mythology Navratri is the time of celebration of divine feminine. 

Durga, Kaali are all different manifestations of the same divine feminine and is associated with protection, strength, motherhood, destruction of evil. 

This piece uses the fall colors to represent this form of Durga Devi, the manifestation of Shakti in all its glory.
